# Requires -Version 5.1
# ==============================================================================
# Script Name  : Get-GroupDeviceIntuneReport.ps1
# Description  : Given an Azure AD / Entra Group ID, pulls all device members
#                from that group, then searches Intune and Azure AD for every
#                device by hostname. Cross-references all records and identifies
#                the single UNIQUE ACTIVE Intune entry per device.
#
#                Produces THREE output files:
#                  1. Full CSV report — one row per entry with verdicts,
#                     GroupAction column, and full cross-reference data
#                  2. BulkRemove TXT — AAD Object IDs to remove from group
#                     (ready for Entra portal Bulk Remove upload)
#                  3. Log file — full transcript of the run
#
#                WHY THIS SCRIPT EXISTS:
#                  A static group may contain stale/duplicate AAD device objects
#                  from old enrollments. This script identifies exactly which
#                  objects should stay in the group (one clean record per device)
#                  and which should be removed — so policy assignment and
#                  compliance reporting are accurate.
#
#                HOW IT WORKS:
#                  1. Detect group type (Security / Intune Device group)
#                  2. Pull all device members from the group (paginated)
#                  3. For each device hostname:
#                     a. Search Intune  — all matching managed device records
#                     b. Search Azure AD — all matching device objects
#                     c. Cross-reference using AADDeviceId
#                     d. Elect ONE "Unique Active" Intune entry per hostname
#                        (newest enrolled date; fallback = most recent last sync)
#                     e. Assign VERDICT and GroupAction per row
#                  4. Export full CSV report
#                  5. Export BulkRemove TXT (Object IDs only)
#                  6. Print console summary + save log
#
#                ACTIVE ENTRY ELECTION (per hostname):
#                  Among all Intune records for a hostname:
#                    Primary  → newest enrolledDateTime
#                    Fallback → most recent lastSyncDateTime
#                              (used when enrolled dates are equal or missing)
#
#                VERDICT per row:
#
#                  Intune rows:
#                    UNIQUE ACTIVE  — elected active Intune record (use for policy)
#                    KEEP           — only one Intune record, no duplicate
#                    DELETE         — older duplicate Intune record
#                    REVIEW         — cannot determine which is newer
#
#                  Azure AD rows:
#                    KEEP (ACTIVE)  — linked to the active Intune record
#                    DELETE         — orphaned AAD object (no Intune link)
#                    REVIEW         — ambiguous — shown in BOTH GroupAction buckets
#
#                GroupAction column:
#                  KEEP IN GROUP      — clean, authoritative record
#                  REMOVE FROM GROUP  — stale/duplicate, safe to remove
#                  REVIEW — KEEP?     — REVIEW row shown as possible keep option
#                  REVIEW — REMOVE?   — REVIEW row shown as possible remove option
#
#                  REVIEW rows appear TWICE in the CSV (once per action option)
#                  so you can decide which line to act on before Bulk Remove.
#
#                BULK REMOVE TXT:
#                  Contains only AAD Object IDs from rows where
#                  GroupAction = "REMOVE FROM GROUP".
#                  Upload directly to Entra portal → Group → Members → Bulk Remove.
#                  REVIEW rows are NOT included — add manually after reviewing CSV.
#
#                CSV COLUMNS:
#                  VERDICT, VerdictReason, GroupAction,
#                  IsUniqueActiveIntuneEntry,
#                  Hostname, Source, SerialNumber,
#                  IntuneDeviceID, AADObjectID, AADDeviceID,
#                  PrimaryUser, EnrolledDate, RegisteredDate,
#                  LastSync, LastActivity, DaysSinceSync,
#                  ComplianceState, ManagementState, OS,
#                  LinkedToIntune, LinkedAADObjectID,
#                  DuplicateCount_Intune, DuplicateCount_AAD
#
#                INPUT:
#                  $GroupID — set in the CONFIGURATION region below.
#
#                OUTPUT FILES (saved to $PSScriptRoot by default):
#                  Get-GroupDeviceIntuneReport_[timestamp].csv
#                  Get-GroupDeviceIntuneReport_[timestamp]_BulkRemove.txt
#                  Get-GroupDeviceIntuneReport_[timestamp].log
#
# Author       : Endpoint Engineering Team
# Team         : Endpoint Engineering — Western Digital
# Version      : 2.0
# Created Date : 2026-04-13
#
# Requirements :
#   - Azure AD App Registration
#   - Graph API Application Permissions (admin consent granted):
#       GroupMember.Read.All                     — read group members
#       DeviceManagementManagedDevices.Read.All  — search Intune records
#       Device.Read.All                          — search Azure AD objects
#   - PowerShell 5.1 or later
#
# Change Log   :
#   v1.0 - 2026-04-13 - Endpoint Engineering Team - Initial release.
#   v2.0 - 2026-04-13 - Endpoint Engineering Team - Added GroupAction column.
#                        REVIEW rows shown twice (KEEP? and REMOVE?) in CSV.
#                        Added BulkRemove TXT export for Entra portal upload.
#                        REVIEW rows excluded from BulkRemove TXT by default.
# ==============================================================================


